template:docs/core/button-group.title: Button Group

Provided some of the blueprintjs button group features as follows. Queries Fun Settings Props Fill Large Minimal Vertical Align text Left Center Right Props Props Description alignText string Text alignment within button. By default, icons and text will be centered within the button. Passing "left" or "right" will align the button text to that side and push icon and rightIcon to either edge. Passing "center" will center the text and icons together. class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. style string Inline html style to parent element. fill boolean Whether the button group should take up the full width of its container. large boolean Whether the child buttons should appear with large styling. minimal boolean Whether the button groups should appear with minimal styling. vertical boolean Whether the button group should appear with vertical styling.

template:docs/core/card.title: Card
template:docs/core/card.text: Card A card is a bounded unit of UI content with a solid background color. Analytical applications User interfaces that enable people to interact smoothly with data, ask better questions, and make better decisions. Explore products Props InteractiveElevation 0 1 2 3 4 double-caret-vertical Elevation Apply an elevation value to a card to apply a drop shadow that simulates height in the UI. Five elevations are supported, from 0 to 4. Props Props Description class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. elevation Elevation0 Controls the intensity of the drop shadow beneath the card: the higher the elevation, the higher the drop shadow. At elevation 0, no drop shadow is applied. interactive booleanfalse Whether the card should respond to user interactions. If set to true, hovering over the card will increase the card's elevation and change the mouse cursor to a pointer. Recommended when onClick is also defined. onClick (e: MouseEvent<HTMLDivElement>) => void Callback invoked when the card is clicked. Recommended when interactive is true.

template:docs/core/check-box.title: CheckBox
template:docs/core/check-box.text: CheckBox A checkbox allows the user to toggle between checked, unchecked, and (rarely) indeterminate states. Assign responsibility Gilad Gray Jason Killian Antoine Llorca Props Disabled Inline Large Align indicator Left Right Props Props Description alignIndicator string Alignment of the indicator within container. The options are left, center, right. checked boolean Whether the control is checked. class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. defaultChecked boolean Whether the control is initially checked (uncontrolled mode). defaultIndeterminate boolean Whether this checkbox is initially indeterminate (uncontrolled mode). disabled boolean Whether the control is non-interactive. indeterminate boolean Whether this checkbox is indeterminate, or "partially checked." The checkbox will appear with a small dash instead of a tick to indicate that the value is not exactly true or false. Note that this prop takes precendence over checked: if a checkbox is marked both checked and indeterminate via props, it will appear as indeterminate in the DOM. inline boolean Whether the control should appear as an inline element. label string Text label for the control. labelElement HtmlElement|string Html Element for check box instead of label. large boolean Whether this control should use large styles. onChange HTMLInputElement Event handler invoked when input value is changed.

template:docs/core/control-group.title: Control group
template:docs/core/control-group.text: Control group A control group renders several distinct form controls as one unit, squaring the borders between them. It supports any number of buttons, text inputs, input groups, and HTML selects as direct children. Hii Props Fill Vertical Props Props Description class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. fill boolean Whether the control group should take up the full width of its container. vertical boolean Whether the control group should appear with vertical styling. Flex layout ControlGroup is a CSS inline flex row (or column if vertical) and provides some modifer props for common flexbox patterns: Enable the fill prop on a control group to make all controls expand equally to fill the available space. Controls will expand horizontally by default, or vertically if the vertical prop is enabled. Add the class Classes.FIXED to individual controls to revert them to their initial sizes. Alternatively, enable the fill prop on specific controls (instead of on the group) to expand them equally to fill the available space while other controls retain their original sizes. You can adjust the specific size of a control with the flex-basis or width CSS properties.

template:docs/core/db-tree.title: Tree
template:docs/core/db-tree.text: Tree Trees display hierarchical data. Props Tree is a stateless component. Its contents are dictated by the contents argument, which is an array of Objects. The tree is multi-rooted if contents contains more than one top-level object. A variety of interaction callbacks are also exposed as args. All interaction callbacks supply a parameter nodePath, which is an array of numbers representing a node's position in the tree. Tree Node content Array objects determine the contents of the tree, appearance, and state of each node in the tree. For example, icon controls the icon displayed for the node, and isExpanded determines whether the node's children are shown. Props Description class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. hasCaret boolean Whether the caret to expand/collapse a node should be shown. If not specified, this will be true if the node has children and false otherwise. Inherited from content.hasCaret icon IconName | MaybeElement The name of a Blueprint icon (or an icon element) to render next to the node's label. id string | number A unique identifier for the node. RequiredInherited from content.id isExpanded boolean Inherited from content.isExpanded label string | Element The main label for the node. RequiredInherited from content.label onClick (node: TreeNode<T>, e: MouseEvent<HTMLDivElement>) => void onCollapse (node: TreeNode<T>, e: MouseEvent<HTMLSpanElement>) => void onDoubleClick (node: TreeNode<T>, e: MouseEvent<HTMLDivElement>) => void onExpand (node: TreeNode<T>, e: MouseEvent<HTMLSpanElement>) => void onMouseEnter (node: TreeNode<T>, e: MouseEvent<HTMLDivElement>) => void onMouseLeave (node: TreeNode<T>, e: MouseEvent<HTMLDivElement>) => void secondaryIcon string A secondary icon that is displayed at the right side of the node. Inherited from content.secondaryIcon

template:docs/core/dialog.title: Dialog Box
template:docs/core/dialog.text: Dialog Box Dialogs present content overlaid over other parts of the UI. Show Dialog Data integration is the seminal problem of the digital age. For over ten years, we’ve helped the world’s premier organizations rise to the challenge. Palantir Foundry radically reimagines the way enterprises interact with data by amplifying and extending the power of data integration. With Foundry, anyone can source, fuse, and transform data into any shape they desire. Business analysts become data engineers — and leaders in their organization’s data revolution. Foundry’s back end includes a suite of best-in-class data integration capabilities: data provenance, git-style versioning semantics, granular access controls, branching, transformation authoring, and more. But these powers are not limited to the back-end IT shop. In Foundry, tables, applications, reports, presentations, and spreadsheets operate as data integrations in their own right. Access controls, transformation logic, and data quality flow from original data source to intermediate analysis to presentation in real time. Every end product created in Foundry becomes a new data source that other users can build upon. And the enterprise data foundation goes where the business drives it. Start the revolution. Unleash the power of data integration with Palantir Foundry. Footer Props Size Default Small Standard Large 72% 560px Vertical Auto focus Enforce focus Has backdrop Use Portal Click outside to close Escape key to close Drawer render from left Props Use the size prop to set the size of the Drawer. This prop sets CSS width if vertical={false} (default) and height otherwise. Constants are available for common sizes: Drawer.SIZE_SMALL = 360px Drawer.SIZE_STANDARD = 50% (default) Drawer.SIZE_LARGE = 90% Props Description autoFocus booleantrue Whether the overlay should acquire application focus when it first opens. backdropClassName string CSS class names to apply to backdrop element. canEscapeKeyClose booleantrue Whether pressing the esc key should invoke onClose. canOutsideClickClose booleantrue Whether clicking outside the overlay element (either on backdrop when present or on document) should invoke onClose. class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. enforceFocus booleantrue Whether the overlay should prevent focus from leaving itself. That is, if the user attempts to focus an element outside the overlay and this prop is enabled, then the overlay will immediately bring focus back to itself. If you are nesting overlay components, either disable this prop on the "outermost" overlays or mark the nested ones usePortal={false}. hasBackdrop booleantrue Whether a container-spanning backdrop element should be rendered behind the contents. isOpen boolean Toggles the visibility of the overlay and its children. This prop is required because the component is controlled. Required onClose (event?: SyntheticEvent<HTMLElement>) => void A callback that is invoked when user interaction causes the overlay to close, such as clicking on the overlay or pressing the esc key (if enabled). Receives the event from the user's interaction, if there was an event (generally either a mouse or key event). Note that, since this component is controlled by the isOpen prop, it will not actually close itself until that args becomes false. portalClassName string Space-delimited string of class names applied to the Portal element if usePortal={true}. size number | stringsize= "50%" CSS size of the drawer. This sets width if vertical={false} (default) and height otherwise. Constants are available for common sizes: SIZE_SMALL = 360px SIZE_STANDARD = 50% SIZE_LARGE = 90% style string CSS styles to apply to the dialog. usePortal booleantrue Whether the overlay should be wrapped in a Portal, which renders its contents in a new element attached to portalContainer prop. This prop essentially determines which element is covered by the backdrop: if false, then only its parent is covered; otherwise, the entire page is covered (because the parent of the Portal is the <body> itself). Set this prop to false on nested overlays (such as Dialog or Popover) to ensure that they are rendered above their parents. vertical booleanfalse Whether the drawer should appear with vertical styling. isLeft booleanfalse Whether the drawer should place position at left side of the screen. Important for dialog box Need to add <div id="destination"> <div> to main application.hbs.The destination Id which is used for handling portal feature.

template:docs/core/input-group.title: Input Group
template:docs/core/input-group.text: Input Group An InputGroup component allows you to add icons and buttons within a text input to expand its functionality. For example, you might use an input group to build a visibility toggle for a password field. The Input tag specifies an input field where the user can enter data. Props Disabled Large Small Intent None Primary Success Warning Danger double-caret-vertical Props The InputGroup component supports one non-interactive icon on the left side and one arbitrary element on the right side. Unlike the CSS approach, InputGroup supports content of any length on the right side (not just icon buttons) because it is able to measure the content and ensure there is always space for it. InputGroup can be used just like a standard input element, in a controlled or uncontrolled fashion. In addition to its own props, it supports all valid props for HTML <input> elements and proxies them to that element in the DOM; the most common ones are detailed below. Props Description class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. style string Inline html style to parent element. disabled boolean Whether the input is non-interactive. Note that rightElement must be disabled separately; this prop will not affect it. intent string Visual intent color to apply to element. Options are primary,success,warning,danger,none. largebooleanWhether this input should use large styles. leftIcon IconName Name of a Blueprint UI icon to left side of input. Default icon position is right iconSize number16 Assign Icon size. large boolean Whether this input should use large styles. Round boolean Whether this input should use round styles. rightIcon IconName Name of a Blueprint UI icon to render after the text. value string Input text. small boolean Whether this input should use small styles. onChange (HTMLElement, string | number | integer)=> void Change event handler. Use event.target.value for new value. onClick (data:string, event: MouseEvent<HTMLElement>) => void Click event handler. onDoubleClick (data:string, event: MouseEvent<HTMLElement>) => void When mouse button double-clicked. onkeyUp (data:string, event: MouseEvent<HTMLElement>) => void When user release a key from input. onBlur (data:string, event: MouseEvent<HTMLElement>) => void When a user leaves an input field. onkeyDown (data:string, event: MouseEvent<HTMLElement>) => void When a user is pressing/holding down a key. leftIconClick (data:string, event: MouseEvent<HTMLElement>) => void Left icon clicked. rightIconClick (data:string, event: MouseEvent<HTMLElement>) => void Right icon clicked. yield value for rightElement props Disabled and readonly input prevents all interaction

template:docs/core/numeric-input.title: Numeric input
template:docs/core/numeric-input.text: Numeric input The NumericInput component provides controls for easily inputting, incrementing, and decrementing numeric values. Interactions Values in numeric inputs can be incremented or decremented using both keyboard and mouse interactions. Keyboard interactions ↑/↓ - change the value by one step (default: ±1) Shift + ↑/↓ - change the value by one major step (default: ±10) Alt + ↑/↓ - change the value by one minor step (default: ±0.1) Mouse interactions Click ⌃/⌄ - change the value by one step (default: ±1) Shift + Click ⌃/⌄ - change the value by one major step (default: ±10) Alt + Click ⌃/⌄ - change the value by one minor step (default: ±0.1) Props Disabled Fill Large Left icon Numeric characters only Select all on focus Select all on increment Minimum value Maximum value Button position Intent Extended example This example shows how NumericInput can be extended beyond its core functionality. It supports the basic interactions above as well as each of the following types of input: Number abbreviations (e.g. 2.1k, -0.3m) Scientific notation (e.g. 2.1e3, -0.3e6) Addition and subtraction expressions (e.g. 3+2, 0.1m - 5k + 1) These special-case inputs are evaluated when Enter is pressed (via a custom onKeyDown callback) and when the field loses focus (via a custom onBlur callback). If the input is invalid when either of these callbacks is trigged, the field will be cleared. This example contains non-core functionality that is meant to demonstrate the extensibility of the `NumericInput` component. The correctness of the custom evaluation code has not been tested robustly. Props Props Description allowNumericCharactersOnly boolean true Whether to allow only floating-point number characters in the field, mimicking the native input[type="number"] . buttonPosition "left" | "right" | "none" "right" The position of the buttons with respect to the input field. clampValueOnBlur boolean false Whether the value should be clamped to [min, max] on blur. The value will be clamped to each bound only if the bound is defined. Note that native input[type="number"] controls do NOT clamp on blur. class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. disabled boolean false Whether the input is non-interactive. fill boolean Whether the numeric input should take up the full width of its container. intent Intent Visual intent color to apply to element. large boolean false If set to true , the input will display with larger styling. This is equivalent to setting Classes.LARGE via className on the parent control group and on the child input group. leftIcon IconName Name of a Blueprint UI icon (or an icon element) to render on the left side of input. majorStepSize number | null 10 The increment between successive values when shift is held. Pass explicit null value to disable this interaction. max number The maximum value of the input. min number The minimum value of the input. minorStepSize number | null 0.1 The increment between successive values when alt is held. Pass explicit null value to disable this interaction. onButtonClick (valueAsNumber: number, valueAsString: string) => void The callback invoked when the value changes due to a button click. onValueChange (valueAsNumber: number, valueAsString: string) => void The callback invoked when the value changes due to typing, arrow keys, or button clicks. placeholder string The placeholder text in the absence of any value. selectAllOnFocus boolean false Whether the entire text field should be selected on focus. selectAllOnIncrement boolean false Whether the entire text field should be selected on increment. stepSize number 1 The increment between successive values when no modifier keys are held. value number | string The value to display in the input field.

template:docs/core/overflow-list.title: Overflow list
template:docs/core/overflow-list.text: Overflow list OverflowList takes a generic list of items and renders as many items as can fit inside itself. Overflowed items that do not fit are collapsed into a single element. The visible items will be recomputed when a resize is detected. The items prop accepts an array of generic objects. The required visibleItemRenderer function which determines the appearance of a visible item. The required overflowRenderer function receives all overflowed items and renders the overflow indicator. This component uses a polyfill for the proposed ResizeObserver API to efficiently detect when its dimensions change. Use the observeParents prop to watch for resizing further up in the DOM tree. Props Collapse from Start End ExampleWidth chevron-up chevron-down Props ResizeSensor requires a single DOM element child and will error otherwise. Props Description className string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. collapseFrom StringSTART(default)| END Which direction the items should collapse from: start or end of the children. This also determines whether overflowRenderer appears before (START) or after (END) the visible items. items Array of objects All items to display in the list. Items that do not fit in the container will be rendered in the overflow instead. Required minVisibleItems number0 The minimum number of visible items that should never collapse into the overflow menu, regardless of DOM dimensions. observeParents booleanfalse If true, all parent DOM elements of the container will also be observed. If changes to a parent's size is detected, the overflow will be recalculated. Only enable this prop if the overflow should be recalculated when a parent element resizes in a way that does not also cause the OverflowList to resize. style CSSProperties CSS properties to apply to the root element. tagName keyof IntrinsicElements"div" HTML tag name for the container element.

This generating different components allows the component to avoid multiple cloning elements. template:docs/core/radio.title: Radio
template:docs/core/radio.text: Radio A radio button typically represents a single option in a mutually exclusive list (where only one item can be selected at a time). Ember-elements provides Radio and RadioGroup components for these two layers. Soup Salad Sandwich Props Disabled Inline Large Align indicator Left Right Props Typically, radio buttons are used in a group to choose one option from several, similar to how a <select> tag contains several <option> tags. As such, you can use the RadioGroup component with a series of Radio children. RadioGroup is responsible for managing state and interaction. Props Description alignIndicator string Alignment of the indicator within container. The options are left , center , right . checked boolean Whether the control is checked. class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. defaultChecked boolean Whether the control is initially checked (uncontrolled mode). disabled boolean Whether the control is non-interactive. inline boolean Whether the control should appear as an inline element. label string Text label for the control. labelElement HtmlElement|string Html Element for radio instead of label. large boolean Whether this control should use large styles. onChange HTMLInputElement Event handler invoked when input value is changed. value string | number Value of this option. Required RadioGroup Props Description class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. disabled boolean Whether the group and all its radios are disabled. Individual radios can be disabled using their disabled prop. inline boolean Whether the radio buttons are to be displayed inline horizontally. label string Optional label text to display above the radio buttons. name string Name of the group, used to link radio buttons together in HTML. If omitted, a unique name will be generated internally. onChange (event: HTMLInputElement) => void Callback invoked when the currently selected radio changes. Use event.target.value to read the currently selected value. This prop is required because this component only supports controlled usage. Required options IOptionProps[] Array of options to render in the group. This prop is mutually exclusive with children: either provide an array of IOptionProps objects or provide <Radio> children elements. selectedValue string | number Value of the selected radio. The child with this value will be :checked. IOptionProps IOptionProps for an option in a list, such as in a <select> or RadioGroup. These props can be spread directly to an <option> or <Radio> element. Props Description class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. disabled boolean Whether this option is non-interactive. label string Label text for this option. If omitted, value is used as the label. value string | number Value of this option. Required

template:docs/core/resizesensor.title: Resize sensor
template:docs/core/resizesensor.text: Resize sensor ResizeSensor is a component that provides a "resize" event for its single DOM element child. It is a thin wrapper around ResizeObserver to provide React bindings. width is rendering @ DOM Props ResizeSensor requires a single DOM element child and will error otherwise. Props Description observeParents booleanfalse If true, all parent DOM elements of the container will also be observed for size changes. The array of entries passed to onResize will now contain an entry for each parent element up to the root of the document. Only enable this prop if a parent element resizes in a way that does not also cause the child element to resize. onResize (entries: IResizeEntry[]) => void Callback invoked when the wrapped element resizes. The entries array contains an entry for each observed element. In the default case (no observeParents), the array will contain only one element: the single child of the ResizeSensor. Note that this method is called asynchronously after a resize is detected and typically it will be called no more than once per frame. Required

template:docs/core/switch.title: Switch
template:docs/core/switch.text: Switch A switch is simply an alternate appearance for a checkbox that simulates on/off instead of checked/unchecked. Privacy setting Props Disabled Inline Large Align indicator Left Right Props Props Description alignIndicator string Alignment of the indicator within container. The options are left,center,right. checked boolean Whether the control is checked. class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. defaultChecked boolean Whether the control is initially checked (uncontrolled mode). disabled boolean Whether the control is non-interactive. inline boolean Whether the control should appear as an inline element. innerLabel string Text to display inside the switch indicator when unchecked. innerLabelChecked string Text to display inside the switch indicator when checked. If innerLabel is provided and this prop is omitted, then innerLabel will be used for both states. label string Text label for the control. labelElement HtmlElement|string Html Element for switch instead of label. large boolean Whether this control should use large styles. onChange HTMLInputElement, checked value Event handler invoked when input value is changed.

template:docs/core/tabs.title: Tabs
template:docs/core/tabs.text: Tabs Tabs is the top-level component responsible for rendering the tab list and coordinating selection. It can be used in controlled mode by providing selectedTabIndex and onChange props, or in uncontrolled mode by optionally providing default SelectedTabIndex and onChange. Current page: Example panel: Ember Ember.js is an open-source JavaScript application framework, based on the model-view-controller (MVC) pattern. It allows developers to create scalable single-page web applications by incorporating common idioms and best practices into the framework. What is your favorite JS framework? Example panel: Angular HTML is great for declaring static documents, but it falters when we try to use it for declaring dynamic views in web-applications. AngularJS lets you extend HTML vocabulary for your application. The resulting environment is extraordinarily expressive, readable, and quick to develop. Example panel: React Lots of people use React as the V in MVC. Since React makes no assumptions about the rest of your technology stack, it's easy to try it out on a small feature in an existing project. Backbone Props Animate indicator Use vertical tabs Render active tab only Tabs The Tabs rendered in order in the tab list, which is a flex container. Tab sub components are managed by the main component (Tabs); clicking one will change selection. Arbitrary other children are simply rendered in order; interactions are your responsibility. Here we avoid manual ID generation of each tab. We know that ember component is generating unique ID. The panel prop is removed from Tab and replaced with yield option for component manipulation. You are able to render Tab contents with help of yield Removed children option from Tab . (children: rendered in a list above the active panel. Can also be set via the title prop.). The yield option is already occupied for panel prop. So we requesting you to use @title prop instead of children. The title supports text along with htmlElments in the form of string. Props Props Description class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. defaultSelectedTabIndex number1 Initial selected tab index, for uncontrolled usage. Note that this prop refers only to <Tab> children; other types of elements are ignored. It accept numeric value from 1 to ..n tab large booleanfalse If set to true, the tab titles will display with larger styling. This will apply large styles only to the tabs at this level, not to nested tabs. onChange (newTabIndex: number, prevTabIndex: number, event: MouseEvent) => void A callback function that is invoked when a tab in the tab list is clicked. renderActiveTabPanelOnly booleanfalse Whether inactive tab panels contents should be removed from the DOM and unmounted . This can be a performance enhancement when rendering many complex panels, but requires careful support for unmounting and remounting. selectedTabIndex number Selected tab index, for controlled usage. Providing this prop will put the component in controlled mode. Unknown index will result in first tab selection (no errors). vertical booleanfalse Whether to show tabs stacked vertically on the left side. Tab Props Description className string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. disabled booleanfalse Whether the tab is disabled. titleClassName string Space-delimited string of class names applied to title tab container. title string | Html element Content of tab title element, rendered in a list above the active panel.

template:docs/core/tag-input.title: Tag input
template:docs/core/tag-input.text: Tag input TagInput addon which is used to add new tags. You are able to add new tags with help of pressingEnter key and some of the features are mentioned as follows. Props Props Description class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. style string Inline html style to parent element. data Array <string> It is an array of string isCloseNotRequired boolean It remove right side cross button from tag input. placeholder string Placeholder text. disabled boolean Whether this action is non-interactive. defaultBgcolor string Html background color for tag elements defaultFgcolor string Foreground color for tag elements. delete (index:number ) => void It return index of deleting item. save (value:string ) => void It return entered value. Tag input additional features While tag input is focused, backspace key can be used to delete a tag which is selected with a light blue border, left and right arrow key can also be used to navigate within the tags, after selection of tag backspace key will delete the tag by calling delete function with id as parameter. each tag has its own delete button which will call delete function with index as parameter. Right cross button will delete all tags.

template:docs/core/tag.title: Tag
template:docs/core/tag.text: Tag Tags are great for lists of strings. Props Active Fill Large Minimal Removable Interactive Round icon Right-Icon Intent None Primary Success Warning Danger double-caret-vertical Props Props Description active booleanfalse Whether the tag should appear in an active state. class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. fill booleanfalse Whether the tag should take up the full width of its container. icon IconName Name of a Blueprint UI icon to render before the text. Default icon position is left iconSize number Size of icon Default icon height is 16 intent string Visual intent color to apply to element. Options are primary,success,warning,danger,none. interactive booleanfalse Whether the tag should visually respond to user interactions. If set to true, hovering over the tag will change its color and mouse cursor. Recommended when onClick is also defined. large booleanfalse Whether this tag should use large styles. minimal booleanfalse Whether this tag should use minimal styles. onClick (e: MouseEvent<HTMLDivElement>) => void Callback invoked when the tag is clicked. Recommended when interactive is true. onRemove (value:string, params:any, e: MouseEvent<HTMLButtonElement>) => void Click handler for remove button. The remove button will only be rendered if this prop is defined. rightIcon IconName Name of a Blueprint UI icon (or an icon element) to render after the children. round booleanfalse Whether this tag should have rounded ends. style string Inline html style to parent element. value string Action text.

template:docs/core/text-area.title: Text area
template:docs/core/text-area.text: Text area Apply Classes.INPUT on a <textarea>, or use the TextArea component. Props Disabled Readonly Larger font size Fill Small font size Intent Props Props Description className string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. fill boolean Whether the text area should take up the full width of its container. growVertically boolean Whether the text area should automatically grow vertically to accomodate content. intent Intent Visual intent color to apply to element. large boolean Whether the text area should appear with large styling. small boolean Whether the text area should appear with small styling. It support common textarea attributes are `id as textAreaId ` , `autofocus ` , `cols ` , `rows ` , `disabled ` , `form ` , `dir ` , `maxlength ` , `name ` , `placeholder ` , `readOnly ` , `required ` , `tabindex ` ,

template:docs/core/tooltip.title: Tooltip
template:docs/core/tooltip.text: Tooltip A tooltip is a lightweight popover for showing additional infromation on hover. Inline text can have this is tool tip Or, hover anywhere over this whole line. This line's tooltip is disabled. This line's tooltip is controlled by external state. Open. Available in the full range of visual intents! Props Props Description content Element | string The content that will be displayed inside of the tooltip. Required defaultIsOpen booleanfalse Initial opened state when uncontrolled. disabled booleanfalse Prevents the popover from appearing when true. intent Intent Visual intent color to apply to element. Options are primary,warning,success,danger isOpen booleanundefined Whether the popover is visible. Passing this prop puts the popover in controlled mode, where the only way to change visibility is by updating this property. If disabled={true}, this prop will be ignored, and the popover will remain closed. targetClassName string Space-delimited string of class names applied to the target element. style string CSS styles to apply to the target.

template:docs/date/date-picker.title: Date Picker
template:docs/date/date-picker.text: Date Picker A DatePicker addon shows a monthly calendar and allows the user to choose a single date. date-picker is built on top of the ember-power-calendar. Props Position when opened (placement) auto left right top bottom double-caret-vertical Minimal popover style Props Props Description class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. style string Inline html style to parent element. onSelect (date: dateObject<moment>) => void date select event handler. Which will return a date object and here need to convert as you need. format string Format of date and default date format is DD/MM/YYYY.It also accept various defferent formats. isDefaultOpen boolean Default open date pop-over . date string | object Date should be '3/4/2018' format or In component.ts date:object = new Date('12/5/2018') startYear number It start the value of years select box . endYear number It limit the value of years select box . minimal boolean Minimal popover style. InputGroupProps Partial<InputGroupProps> & object InputGroupProps for InputGroup component. onkeyDown (data:string, event: MouseEvent<HTMLElement>) => void When a user is pressing/holding down a key on input. Props Description class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. style string Inline html style to parent element. disabled boolean Whether the input is non-interactive. Note that rightElement must be disabled separately; this prop will not affect it. intent string Visual intent color to apply to element. Options are primary,success,warning,danger,none. largebooleanWhether this input should use large styles. leftIcon IconName Name of a Blueprint UI icon to left side of input. Default icon position is right iconSize number16 Assign Icon size. round boolean Whether this input should use round styles. rightIcon IconName Name of a Blueprint UI icon to render after the text. small boolean Whether this input should use small styles.

template:docs/date/date-range-picker.title: Date Range Picker
template:docs/date/date-range-picker.text: Date Range Picker A DateRangePicker It shows two sequential month calendars and lets the user select a single range of days. Props Position when opened (placement) auto left right top bottom double-caret-vertical Minimal popover style Shortcuts The menu on the left of the calendars provides "shortcuts" that allow users to quickly select common date ranges. The preset shortcuts can be seen in the example above. They are as follows: Past week Past month Past 3 months Past 6 months Past year Past 2 years Custom shortcuts use the following interface: Props Props Description class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. style string Inline html style to parent element. onSelect (date: dateObject<{start and end date}>) => void date select event handler. format string Format of date and default date format is DD/MM/YYYY isDefaultOpen boolean Default open date pop-over . range object Range is an object which contains start date and end date. ex: range: object = {start: new Date('3/1/2018'),end: new Date('3/20/2018')}; Required startYear number It start the value of years select box . endYear number It limit the value of years select box . minimal boolean Minimal popover style. InputGroupProps Partial<InputGroupProps> & object InputGroupProps for InputGroup component. onkeyDown (data:string, event: MouseEvent<HTMLElement>) => void When a user is pressing/holding down a key on input. onClick (open:boolean) => void Input click event handler. Note that rightElement must be disabled separately; this prop will not affect it. intent string Visual intent color to apply to element. Options are primary,success,warning,danger,none. largebooleanWhether this input should use large styles. leftIcon IconName Name of a Blueprint UI icon to left side of input. template:docs/introduction/quickstart.title: Quickstart
template:docs/introduction/quickstart.text: Quickstart Installation ember install ember-elements Styles @import "ember-elements-styles"; follow addon test style folder if other scss files required(`docs-app.scss`,`ember-cli-addon-docs.scss`)! Browser support Ember-elements supports Chrome, Firefox, Safari, IE 11, and Microsoft Edge. You may experience degraded visuals in IE. IE 10 and below are unsupported due to their lack of support for CSS Flexbox Layout.

template:docs/select/multi-select.title: MultiSelect
template:docs/select/multi-select.text: MultiSelect The MultiSelect addon which provide an option for choosing multiple items from option list. The multiple values are considered as each tags alongs with default background color and close button. You are able to change background and foreground color as mentioned below. The multiselect contain right close button which is used to remove all tags elements. Props Position when opened (placement) auto left right top bottom double-caret-vertical Minimal popover style Minimal tag style Props Props Description class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. style string Inline html style to parent element. data Array <string> It is an array of string which contains options for multi-select box selected Array <string> It is an array of string which contains default selected options for multi-select box placeholder string Placeholder text for multi-select box disabled boolean Whether this action is non-interactive. isDBrequired boolean It add cross icon at right corner of multi-select. isDefaultOpen boolean Default open select pop-over . onSelect (date: Array<string>) => void Selected options from multi-select box. onDelete (date: Array<string>) => void Return array of object after deletion of tag elements. minimalPopover boolean Minimal popover style. multi-select box additional features There are 6 main keys used to interact with multiselect box up & down navigation Key : navigate within the suggest box. left & right navigation Key :navigate within the selected items inside tag input. enter Key :select an item from suggest box. backspace Key : delete the search keyword and delete selected item inside tag input. NOTE: use up & down key to navigate suggest item and later enter to select. same way use left & right to navigate tags and later backspace to delete. multi select box is by default 100% in width.
